OVERALL LAYOUT NOTES:

Screen is horizontally scrollable 
if needed on smaller displays 
but ideally fits in one view 
on a standard widescreen.

Stages 1-5 are equal size nodes.
Stages 6 and 7 are slightly 
smaller as they sit as 
two branches of the Y-fork.

All connecting lines have 
animated moving dots 
flowing left to right 
continuously — showing 
live data movement through 
the platform at all times.

Each node has a subtle 
glowing border animation — 
not distracting but alive.

The regulatory live feed 
inside Stage 4 and the 
live data indicator inside 
Stage 6 are the only 
pulsing elements — 
drawing attention to 
the real-time data aspect.

